---
const install = "curl -fsSL https://volt-cli.dev/install.sh | sh";
const title = "Volt — a fast, hackable coding agent for your terminal";
const description =
  "Volt is an open-source coding agent CLI: multi-provider, extensible with skills and packages, and reachable from your phone over end-to-end encrypted remote access.";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://volt-cli.dev/" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="nav">
      <a class="brand" href="/">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="22" height="22" aria-hidden="true"><path fill="currentColor" d="M13 2 4.5 13.5H11L9.5 22 19 9.5h-6.5L13 2z"/></svg>
        volt
      </a>
      <nav>
        <a href="/docs/">Docs</a>
        <a href="/docs/quickstart/">Quickstart</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/hansjm10/Volt">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <p class="badge">Preview — public beta gates in progress</p>
        <h1>A coding agent that lives in your terminal,<br />not in someone else's cloud.</h1>
        <p class="sub">
          Volt is an open-source coding agent CLI. Bring your own model — Anthropic, OpenAI,
          or any provider — extend it with skills, extensions, and packages, and keep your
          credential storage and tool execution on your own machine.
        </p>
        <div class="install" id="install-box">
          <code>{install}</code>
          <button id="copy-btn" aria-label="Copy install command">Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="install-alt">
          or <code>npm install -g --ignore-scripts @hansjm10/volt-coding-agent@beta</code>
          &nbsp;·&nbsp; Windows: <code>irm volt-cli.dev/install.ps1 | iex</code>
        </p>
        <div class="cta">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/docs/quickstart/">Get started</a>
          <a class="btn" href="/docs/">Read the docs</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="features">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Your terminal, your rules</h3>
          <p>
            A fast TUI with differential rendering, configurable keybindings, themes, and
            session management with compaction. Works in tmux, over SSH, even on Termux.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Any model, any provider</h3>
          <p>
            A unified multi-provider LLM API under the hood. Use hosted providers or point
            Volt at custom models and endpoints — switching is a setting, not a rewrite.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Take it with you</h3>
          <p>
            Pair your phone once and open live sessions on your workstation from anywhere —
            over end-to-end encrypted Iroh connections. Provider credentials stay on the
            host, and repository access remains host-controlled.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Hackable by design</h3>
          <p>
            Volt ships with powerful defaults and skips the bloat. Add what you need with
            skills, extensions, prompt templates, and installable Volt packages — or ask
            Volt to build them for you.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Supply chain, taken seriously</h3>
          <p>
            Exact-pinned dependencies, shrinkwrapped releases, installs with lifecycle
            scripts disabled, and documented containerization patterns when you want hard
            boundaries.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Scriptable and embeddable</h3>
          <p>
            Drive Volt programmatically with the SDK, RPC mode, or a JSON event stream.
            Build your own tools on the same runtime the CLI uses.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="remote">
        <h2>Start on your desk. Finish from anywhere.</h2>
        <p>
          <code>volt remote host</code> exposes a local Volt runtime to your paired iPhone
          without a Volt account. Connection traffic may traverse configured Iroh relays,
          but session payloads remain end-to-end encrypted. Register workspaces by name,
          scan a QR code once, and your sessions show up as tabs on your phone with live
          transcripts, notifications, and Live Activities.
        </p>
        <a class="btn" href="/docs/usage/#remote-access-over-iroh-preview">How remote access works</a>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <p>
        Maintained and distributed by
        <a href="https://github.com/hansjm10">Jordan Hans</a>. Derived from
        <a href="https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono">Mario Zechner's Pi project</a>
        under the MIT License. Built in the open at
        <a href="https://github.com/hansjm10/Volt">github.com/hansjm10/Volt</a>.
      </p>
      <nav>
        <a href="/docs/">Docs</a>
        <a href="/docs/security/">Security</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/hansjm10/Volt/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">Contributing</a>
      </nav>
    </footer>

    <script>
      const btn = document.getElementById("copy-btn");
      const cmd = document.querySelector("#install-box code")?.textContent ?? "";
      btn?.addEventListener("click", async () => {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(cmd);
        btn.textContent = "Copied";
        setTimeout(() => (btn.textContent = "Copy"), 1500);
      });
    </script>

    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #0c0f0a;
        --panel: #14181070;
        --border: #2a3222;
        --text: #e6ebe0;
        --muted: #9aa78d;
        --accent: #a3e635;
        --accent-dim: #4d7c0f;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; }
      body {
        background: var(--bg);
        background-image: radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 50% at 50% -10%, #1a2411, transparent);
        color: var(--text);
        font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      code { font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
      a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }

      .nav {
        display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
        max-width: 62rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem;
      }
      .brand {
        display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem;
        font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--text);
      }
      .brand svg { color: var(--accent); }
      .nav nav { display: flex; gap: 1.4rem; }
      .nav nav a { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; }
      .nav nav a:hover { color: var(--text); }

      main { max-width: 62rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem; }

      .hero { text-align: center; padding: 4.5rem 0 4rem; }
      .badge {
        display: inline-block; padding: 0.25rem 0.8rem; border-radius: 99px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--accent);
        font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 1.4rem; background: var(--panel);
      }
      h1 { font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 4.5vw, 2.8rem); line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
      .sub { color: var(--muted); max-width: 44rem; margin: 1.2rem auto 2rem; font-size: 1.08rem; }

      .install {
        display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;
        background: #0a0d08; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem; max-width: 100%;
      }
      .install code { color: var(--accent); font-size: 0.95rem; overflow-x: auto; white-space: nowrap; }
      .install button {
        background: var(--accent); color: #0c0f0a; border: 0; border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 0.35rem 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      .install button:hover { background: #bef264; }
      .install-alt { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 0.8rem; }
      .install-alt code { color: var(--muted); }

      .cta { display: flex; gap: 0.8rem; justify-content: center; margin-top: 2rem; }
      .btn {
        display: inline-block; padding: 0.6rem 1.3rem; border-radius: 8px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text); font-weight: 600;
      }
      .btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent-dim); }
      .btn.primary { background: var(--accent); color: #0c0f0a; border-color: var(--accent); }
      .btn.primary:hover { background: #bef264; }

      .features {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(17rem, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem; padding-bottom: 4rem;
      }
      .card {
        border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.4rem;
        background: var(--panel);
      }
      .card h3 { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; }
      .card p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; }

      .remote {
        text-align: center; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 3rem 2rem; margin-bottom: 5rem; background: var(--panel);
      }
      .remote h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
      .remote p { color: var(--muted); max-width: 42rem; margin: 0 auto 1.6rem; }
      .remote code { color: var(--accent); }

      footer {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 2rem 1.5rem; color: var(--muted);
        display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem;
        max-width: 62rem; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 0.9rem;
      }
      footer nav { display: flex; gap: 1.2rem; }

      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .install { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; align-items: stretch; text-align: center; }
        .cta { flex-wrap: wrap; }
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
